Overall Data Flow
Phase 1: LOADING (Matrix Fill)
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Input Data → Matrix A RAM (16 addresses)               │
│ Input Data → Matrix B RAM (16 addresses)               │
│ Instruction ROM → Programmed with microcode            │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

Phase 2: COMPUTATION (Matrix Multiplication)
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ For each multiplication operation:                     │
│   1. Counter → Address for A RAM                       │
│   2. Counter → Address for B RAM                       │
│   3. A RAM → REG_A                                     │
│   4. B RAM → REG_B                                     │
│   5. REG_A × REG_B → ACC                               │
│   6. ACC accumulates results for each output element   │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

Phase 3: STORAGE (Result Save)
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ For each output element:                               │
│   1. ACC → Result RAM (address 0-3)                   │
│   2. Clear ACC for next result                        │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘


Instruction Mnemonics
Mnemonic	OP Code	Description
NOP	0000	No operation
LDA	0001	Load Matrix A to REG_A
LDB	0010	Load Matrix B to REG_B
LDK	0011	Load constant to REG_C
MAC	0100	Multiply + Accumulate
STORE	0101	Store ACC to Result RAM
CLR	0110	Clear Accumulator
JMP	0111	Jump to address
HALT	1000	Stop execution

